# Cross-device companion prompts (PC ↔ Mac)

This repo runs on **Windows PC** (live server, Electron, Cloudflare, player data) and **MacBook** (Xcode, Capacitor iOS builds, TestFlight). GitHub syncs code; **companion prompt files** sync the *other half* of a task.

## When you MUST write a companion prompt

After completing (or partially completing) work, if **the other device still needs changes** for the feature to work end-to-end, update the correct pending file:

| You are on | Other device needs | Write to |
|------------|-------------------|----------|
| PC (Windows) | Mac / iOS / Xcode | `docs/cross-device/pending-on-mac.md` |
| Mac | PC server / Electron / tunnel / website | `docs/cross-device/pending-on-pc.md` |

**Trigger examples (PC → Mac):** new/changed `server/mobile-*.js` API, new WebSocket fields, Hangman Python API changes, env vars iOS must use, IPA rebuild needed, chat/UI contract changes for `hangman v2/iOS/app/` or native Crash Swift.

**Trigger examples (Mac → PC):** iOS app expects new endpoint, proxy path, CORS/header, IPA copied to `releases/ipa/`, Capacitor source changes that need server deploy.

**No companion file** if the task is single-device only (e.g. PC data failsafes, Mac-only Xcode signing).

## Pending file format (required)

Replace the entire file with YAML frontmatter + markdown body:

```markdown
---
cross_device_status: pending
from_device: pc
target_device: mac
created_at: 2026-05-23T14:30:00Z
title: Short task name
related_paths:
  - server/mobile-cosmetics.js
  - hangman v2/iOS/app/src/...
---

# Mac companion task: <title>

## Context
What changed on the other device and why Mac work is needed.

## Do on this device
1. Step-by-step actions (paths, commands, Xcode steps).
2. Include exact API URLs, headers (`X-Client-App`), env vars.

## Verify
- curl / build / device test checklist

## When done
- Set `cross_device_status: done` in frontmatter
- `./scripts/sync-push.sh` (Mac) or `.\scripts\sync-push.ps1` (PC)
```

Use **`cross_device_status: pending`** until the receiving device finishes. Then set **`done`**.

## After writing a companion prompt

Tell the user clearly:

1. **This device:** run sync-push with a commit message.
2. **Other device:** sync-pull, then run `run-pending-task` script OR Agent chat:
   > Run the pending cross-device task in @docs/cross-device/pending-on-mac.md
   (or `pending-on-pc.md` on Windows)

## When you RECEIVE a pending task

If the user says "run pending", "cross-device task", or `@docs/cross-device/pending-on-*.md`:

1. Read the pending file; confirm `cross_device_status: pending`.
2. Execute the task completely on **this** device only.
3. Mark `cross_device_status: done` and push via sync-push.
4. If your work creates **new** needs on the other device, write the reverse pending file.

## Architecture reminders

- **PC live stack:** `run-electron-cloudflare.bat` — Node **3847**, Hangman **19876**, `https://y666suf.com`
- **Player data:** `data/points.live.json` — PC only, never commit
- **iOS source:** `hangman v2/iOS/app/` (Capacitor); Crash may be separate Swift repo — still write companion prompt if API contract changes
- **IPAs:** not in git — copy to `releases/ipa/` on PC after Mac archive
